rComments: People take IMM340 expecting it to be like IMM250 without understanding that the latter is meant to be a bird course, while the former is a rigorous introduction to immunology intended for pursuing future coursework/grad school. Unfortunately, people have associated difficult coursework with a poor instructor, which is far from the case for Dr. M.

It is very difficult for me to understand his lectures. There are three lecturers in this course, and two of them are with strong accents. Be ready to spend time on listening to recordings again and again. He likes to talk about materials that are not on the slides.
Personally, I can't understand half of what he is saying because he is mumbling most of times and he has very thick French accent. At first, I thought he was speaking french.......
His accent is really thick which makes it hard to follow in class. He also goes into a lot of detail without first going over the picture. Made immunology my least favourite course of third year.
